metadata.name: The day the forest got its soul back
metadata.description:
A forest fairy fell in love with a man
Who left her for another's hand
Lonely and brokenhearted, she cursed him 
But it cost her her soul

Only a child with gentle hands
And a heart to change the world
Could lift the curse 
And return her soul to the forest
Where her resting stone lay
A thousand years late
